      <bioghist id="aspace_5ad77bd416b7ff819c34d0d0c32869c5">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Francis William Crandall was born on Janurary 13, 1889, in Westfield, New York. He graduated from Yale University in 1911. After working in the lumber industry in the state of Washington, he relocated to Pittsburgh during the Depression. Crandall was a banker until his retirement in 1952. He died in 1959.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_942f81d2c92b78b4b56a2c5d9f4b3aa5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of typed letters written by Francis William Crandall to his parents while making the "grand tour" of Europe, Africa, and Asia. An edited version with notes and illustrations is also included. Highlights include a description of a safari in East Africa and attendance at a durbar in India.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
